'''Breedo''' was a [[Rodian/Legends|Rodian]] enforcer<ref name="Rogues Gallery" /> thought to be a cousin of the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] [[Greedo/Legends|Greedo]].<ref name="Official Game Secrets" /> In the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]],<ref name="32 BBY">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] to the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]].</ref> the Rodian watched the [[Boonta Eve Classic/Legends|Boonta Eve Classic]] [[Podracing/Legends|podrace]] from the [[Toydarian/Legends|Toydarian]] junk dealer [[Watto/Legends|Watto's]] [[Watto's box|private box]] in the [[Mos Espa Grand Arena/Legends|Mos Espa Grand Arena]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].<ref name="The Phantom Menace" /> In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="0 BBY">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' dates the events of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] to the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]]. As ''[[Super Star Wars]]'' is an adaptation of the events of ''A New Hope'', it can be determined that ''Super Star Wars'' must also take place in 0 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]].</ref> Breedo was at [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]] in Tatooine's [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] when Greedo was [[Death/Legends|killed]] by the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].<ref name="Official Game Secrets" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Breedo seems to be Greedo's blue cousin.|''Super Star Wars Official Game Secrets''|<ref name="Official Game Secrets" />}}
[[File:Breedo_SSW.jpg|200px|thumb|left|Breedo in ''Super Star Wars'']]
Breedo first appeared as multiple enemies in the ''[[Super Star Wars]]'' video game, during the Cantina level. The character appears to be a recolored version of the game's Greedo character without ears or head spikes, more resembling a [[Duros/Legends|Duros]] with its red eyes and blue skin.<ref name="SSW">''[[Super Star Wars]]''</ref>

The game's manual does not show or mention the character, but the ''[[Super Star Wars Official Game Secrets]]'' book names the enemy and suggests they are Greedo's cousin.<ref name="Official Game Secrets" /> Years later, a Rodian character first seen in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''Star Wars'': Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] was identified as Breedo.<ref name="Rogues Gallery" />

